ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
AASPIRE Participant Type / Version Administered
Notes: 1= Direct Report (DR); 2= Direct Report - Supported (DR-S); 3= Caregiver Report (CR)

ElementDescription: (Caregiver Report) The next set of questions are about how the autistic person thinks about their gender. Do you have enough information from the autistic person to answer the questions?
Which of the following (Direct Report: is most true for you / Caregiver Report: do you think is most true for them) when thinking about (your/their) gender?
Notes: 1= (Direct Report: I think of myself / Caregiver Report: They think of themselves) as a woman. This could include being a woman, young woman, trans woman or girl (but it does not need to be all those things); 2= (I think of myself/They think of themselves) as a man. This could include being a man, young man, guy, trans man, or boy (but it does not need to be all those things); 3= Neither are true, both are true, it is complicated, or I cannot pick one
